section.section:
The campaign shall:
Reach out to the general public and specific populations determined to be at high risk for contracting Fetal Alcohol Syndrome;
Disseminate the information about Fetal Alcohol Syndrome through written materials, television, radio, posters, or any other medium the Secretary considers appropriate and effective for conveying the information;
Distribute informational materials free of charge to prenatal clinics and to establishments that serve alcoholic beverages; and
Include any other matter that the Secretary considers appropriate.
